neighborhood_overview: Connections to Copenhagen centre is very easy, but Hellerup itself also has about everything to offer. Strandvejen is perfect for shopping in either designer flagship stores or one of the many convenience stores. Our favourite cafe "Coffee Collective" or "Emmerys" is right around the corner. Enjoy your breakfast here or buy it to bring home from one of the many prima organic bakerys within walking distance. Do as the inhabitants of Hellerup and enjoy a traditional freshly made ice cream from the shops of Strandvejen and take a stroll down to the idyllic Hellerup Harbour. Here you also find the local sandy beach. It is safe for children and an everyday swim in the summertime is a must! Parks for recreation, playing or excercise are close by.
notes: We have a cat living in the apartment though it will not be around during your stay. The apartment will be cleaned before your arrival, but if you are highly allergic, it might be useful to know.
transit: Connections to Copenhagen city centre are many and very easy. Take either the bus 1A (leaves every 10 min. just around the corner) directly to city centre or use the train from Hellerup Station 5 min. walk away. From here you can also take trains directly to the airport. We recommend a trainride towards north for either Louisiana Museum of Modern Art or Dyrehaven, a major park with wild living deers and the beautiful Eremitage Castle.
